<div class="white_box_shadow"><img src="/media/13067062/levi_northern-lights.jpg" alt="northernlightshero" data-udi="umb://media/5ad871801d094af8a47add157d58fd3b" />
<h2>Overnight stays</h2>
<p>High on your bucket list is the Northern Lights or Aurora Borealis - a beautiful, natural light display seen high in the northern hemisphere of our earth.  </p>
<p>To try and <a data-udi="umb://document/d74c19a439d14879bf5ef27c8fe10028" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d74c19a439d14879bf5ef27c8fe10028}" title="How to photograph the Northern Lights">catch this magical moment</a> on your Lapland adventure, it is worth booking one of our purpose-designed accommodation options for a nights stay. </p>
<p>Don’t worry about trying to stay awake into the early hours, all our accommodation options provide a wake-up call when the light display is overhead to ensure you don’t miss a moment. </p>
<p>Depending on your preference you can book a cosy igloo for 2 or a comfy cabin to include the children. </p>
<p>Our excursions are added extras you can book as part of your Lapland holiday.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">
<div class="c-card c-card--generic c-card--generic-shadow">
<h2>Bookable on a Levi Lapland holiday:</h2>
<br /><img src="/media/13094890/smaller-glass-igloo.jpg" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/6da9931b72d84eec90f70b847fa58b79" />
<h3>What’s included in Glass Igloo excursion</h3>
<p>Just 10 minutes from Levi, this amazing accommodation is equipped with a thermal glass roof for maximum Northern Light viewing and includes a choice of Glass Igloo: </p>
<p><strong>Superior Igloos</strong> are about 23m² and located on the side of the fell. They have motorised twin beds to make the most unobstructed views of the sky, plus a sofa bed for two children.</p>
<p><strong>Prime Superior Igloos</strong> are about 23m² and are located in the front or second row. They have motorised twin beds. Igloos with extra beds are available on request, please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Suite Igloos</strong> are the largest igloo type at about 53m², situated in the front row. They have a King size double bed and two extra beds for 2 children (under 13 years old), lounge area with dining table and chairs, speciality coffee maker, minibar (payable locally) and private terrace with outdoor whirlpool. These igloos are available on request, please call to book.</p>
<ul>
<li>Transfers to and from your accommodation included</li>
<li>Overnight stay in a thermal glass igloo on bed and breakfast</li>
<li>Optional Half-Board upgrade, 3 courses starter, main &amp; dessert  – Caters for Vegetarian, Vegan, Gluten Free &amp; Dairy Free (customers must advise at the time of booking)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Made from thermal glass, no condensation</li>
<li>Unobstructed views of the night sky above</li>
<li>Private bathroom with shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bathrobes &amp; slippers</li>
<li>Small kitchen with microwave, kettle, fridge</li>
<li>Bluetooth</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Restaurant</li>
<li>Bar</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">
<div class="c-card c-card--generic c-card--generic-shadow">
<h2>Bookable on a 7 Night Muotka Lapland holiday:</h2>
<br /><img src="/media/13078541/aurora-cabin-glass-roof-1.jpg" alt="auroracabin" data-udi="umb://media/1480d98f71cd4cd692ea6dc693e31911" />
<h3>What’s included in Muotka Aurora Cabin excursion</h3>
<p>Upgrade one night of your stay at Wilderness Hotel Muotka to a semi-glass roof Aurora Cabin. Admire the star-filled sky from the comfort of your bed. The laser-heated glass roof opens up to the northern sky - here you'll have the chance to witness the amazing spectacle of the Northern Lights.</p>
<p>Aurora Cabins sleep 1-4 people (Maximum 3 adults, or 2 adults and 1-2 children). All cabins include twin or double bed and have the possibility of adding an extra bed. They have a bathroom with a shower. Aurora cabin upgrades will be on the first or last night of your stay and will be advised when you arrive in resort.</p>
<ul>
<li>Transfers to and from your accommodation included</li>
<li>Overnight stay in an Aurora Cabin on bed and breakfast</li>
<li>Optional half board upgrade (dietary requirements must be advised at the time of booking)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Laser heated sky windows</li>
<li>Private bathroom with shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Fridge</li>
<li>Kettle</li>
<li>Minibar (payable locally)</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Aurora alerts via the in cabin tablet</li>
<li>Restaurant</li>
<li>Bar</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13065318/where-to-see-the-northern-lights-1.jpg" alt="northernlightsbook" data-udi="umb://media/7355ca24703743769e56dcdf7a6cf1bc" /></p>
<h3>How to book your Northern Lights Adventure:<span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></h3>
<p><span>You can add excursions to your holiday package via your '<a href="https://my.inghams.co.uk/login">My Booking</a>' portal or you can speak to a member of our UK based team on <span class="InfinityNumber">01483 791 111.</span></span></p>
<p><strong>Please note:</strong> Overnight stays: These can be pre-booked but the exact day of the week will be confirmed within 3 working days of booking, as all reservations are subject to availability.</p>
<p> </p>
</div>
</div>
